3. VALUE STUDY — The selected silhouette refined to a value-only study. Three to five values, no color. Proves the form reads before color enters.

4. COLOR EXPLORATION — Three to five color variations of the same value study. Different palettes for the same form. Proves the color was chosen, not stumbled into.

