Ikko Tanaka — Japanese designer who treats type as image. Letters become shapes; shapes become characters; characters become posters. The visual vocabulary builds itself out of typography.

Paul Rand — The IBM posters and broader corporate identity work. Reductive geometry, single-color punch, type and image fused into one mark.

