Background — the far distance. Lowest contrast, least detail, often desaturated and shifted toward the ambient hue. This is where mood lives — the looming storm, the distant city, the empty sky.

Each plane carries different narrative weight. A character in the foreground is the subject of the story. The same character moved to the midground becomes part of a scene. Moved to the background, they become a detail of a world.

