2. Time progression — image 2 occurs after image 1
3. Spatial continuity — image 2 shows the same world (or a connected world) as image 1

For animation, this happens at 24 frames per second — fast enough that the eye perceives continuous motion through the persistence of vision. For comics, storyboards, and 3-panel narratives, this happens at one frame at a time — slow enough that each image has to do significant narrative work.`,
